---
// src/pages/privacy-policy.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy - MoneyInFuture"
  description="MoneyInFuture privacy policy: no tracking cookies, no analytics. Calculator preferences are stored locally in your browser only and never leave your device."
>
  <div class="calculator-header">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="calculator-description">Last updated: June 2026</p>
  </div>

  <section class="seo-content" style="max-width: 760px;">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>MoneyInFuture is built around a simple principle: your financial data is yours. We do not collect, store,
      or transmit any personal or financial information that you enter into our calculators.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.75rem; line-height: 2;">
      <li>Investment amounts, income, or expense figures you enter</li>
      <li>Calculator inputs or outputs</li>
      <li>Personal identification information</li>
      <li>Device identifiers or fingerprints</li>
      <li>Browsing history on this site</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cookies</h2>
    <p>MoneyInFuture does not use tracking cookies of any kind. All preference data is stored exclusively in
      your browser's <code>localStorage</code> — this data never leaves your device and is never sent to any server.
      <strong>localStorage is completely different from cookies</strong>: it is never transmitted with HTTP requests
      and is only accessible to JavaScript running on the same domain.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Analytics</h2>
    <p>We do not use Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, or any third-party analytics service. There are no tracking
      scripts on this website.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Third-Party Libraries</h2>
    <p>Some pages may load MathJax (a mathematical formula renderer) from a CDN when TeX formulas are present.
      This is the only external network request made by the site. MathJax does not collect personal data. All
      other JavaScript (engine.js, shared.js, html2canvas, jsPDF) is served from the same domain.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Local Storage</h2>
    <p>We store the following keys in your browser's localStorage to improve your experience. None of this data
      is transmitted anywhere:</p>
    <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.75rem; line-height: 2;">
      <li><code>theme</code> — your preferred light/dark mode</li>
      <li><code>moneyinfuture_finance_level</code> — your selected Finance Profile Level (Simple, Investor, or Professional)</li>
      <li><code>moneyinfuture_onboarding_completed</code> — whether the welcome level-selection popup has been shown</li>
      <li><code>moneyinfuture_user_prefs</code> — calculator display preferences (sliders, words, color coding, graph, table, inflation, taxation, decimal places)</li>
      <li><code>moneyinfuture_shared_prefs</code> — last-used return rate, years, and inflation rate across calculators</li>
      <li><code>sidebar-collapsed</code> — sidebar layout preference</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">You can clear all saved preferences at any time from the
      <a href="/finance-levels.html">Finance Profile Levels</a> page using the "Reset Preferences" button,
      or by clearing your browser's site data for this domain.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy as the site evolves. The "last updated" date at the top of this page reflects
      when it was last revised.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy, please <a href="/contact.html">contact us</a>.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
